FAST-RISING Afrobeats star Koredianx is warming his way into the hearts of Afropop lovers all over the country and abroad with his new love single ‘Omo Tosan’. The melodious tune with a mix of RnB and Afrobeats rhythm has driven itself up the music charts and is currently gathering listenership on music streaming platforms and radio airwaves. Featuring fellow Jamika Entertainment music label artist Yung Bos, the song lyrics talks about the love the artists have for a mysterious beautiful woman.   The Rise of Igbinogun premieres, gets StarTimes backing     Many talented youths wasting in Niger Delta, says Babylon     Pasuma, Murphy Afolabi, others attend Malaika’s…   In a chat with Koredianx on the inspiration behind the record, he said it was just his way of showing appreciation to the beauty of his female fans and supporters. “Inspiration for the songs comes from all the support I get from my female fans, I choose to drop it on the same week as the international women’s day to show my appreciation to them”, said Koredianx Omo Tosan’ is the second song released under the Jamika Entertainment music label in 2022 and the entertainment company is assuring their fans that more exciting songs are coming throughout the year to keep them entertained.